				<td colspan="2" align="left"><div class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Yunus wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Lets say for the sake of disscusion that Bush loses the next election.  
<br />

<br />
Will terrorism Increase because the terrorists are no longer afraid of there countries being invaded?
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The problem with this, though, is that most terrorists do not have a home country per se.  As it has been mentioned, there is no country Al Queda, no country that is Taliban.  Sure, they may hang out in Afghanistan, Lbya, Syria, Iraq, etc but they truely may not have a country of their own.
<br />

<br />
I do think, however, that if somebody such as Dean is elected president we could see an increase in attacks.  The Middle East seems to have learned something of a lesson in not to play with Republican presidents.  For instance, Carter had that nightmare of a hostage situation, Reagen came to office and *bam* the hostages were released.  George H. Bush kinda but the halt on Iraq in '90-'91, and obviously you can see what the current president is doing in Iraq now.
<br />

<br />
I think that leaders of various countries (e.g. Qaddafi) may think to themselves that with Bush in office they really would rather not be tied to any terrorist attacks against the US.  Syria, Libya, and Iran sure as hell do not want to be invaded by the US and to ensure their safety I would wager they would tell The Local Terrorist 414 do not carry out any attacks against the US at this time.
<br />

<br />
Again, if Dean would get elected and pull US troops out of the middle east, then hey it would be a great opportunity for terrorists to take advantage of the situation.
<br />

<br />
That sums up my point, I suppose:  being able to take advantage of the situation.  When you have hundreds of thousands  of American troops at your door step, you don't want to do anything to @#%$ them off.  However, if they hightail it home and the Commander in Chief will not deploy them again, then it would be advantageous at that point in time to carry out any attacks.<span class="gensmall"></span>


