<span style="text-decoration: underline">Did/does the invasion of Iraq motivate or deter Islamic terrorists?</span> The jury is still out on this one. I would like to believe that it does and will. 
<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Will the presence or absence of bush make a difference in Islamic terrorism?</span>
<br />
Both Islamic and Christian fundamentalists consider the USA to be the great satan. I doubt the presence or absence of bush will mean didly squat to the Islamic terrorists. 
<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Will the presence or absence of bush make a difference in Domestic terrorism?</span>
<br />
Domestic terrorists are and will be encouraged by an administration that supports many similar values of the terrorists. Domestic terrorists get support from the media such as </span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Ann Coulter wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">My only regret with Timothy McVeigh is he did not go to the New York Times Building.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.observer.com/pages/story.asp?ID=6258" target="_blank" class="postlink">Source</a>. Interesting. What she is saying is that she approves of McVeigh's actions, and only disagrees in the choice of target. What she is saying is that murdering Americans is acceptable. Pure hypocracy. But what do you expect from someone who wants to establish death camps for liberals (read Treason for the references). This is the sort of thing that is both supporting the bush administration and getting support from the bush administration. Putting a stop to domestic terrorism will need to start with their media wing: limbaugh, coulter, fox news, cbn, savage and oreilly. What about leftist terrorists? They have been marginalized for years and lack their own TV network. Think about how different the dial on your tv would be if they had their own TV and radio networks like the right wing terrorists do? The PETA network? The earth first tv network? nation of islam tv network? There is no kkk tv network, but if you chat with a klansman, they all love savage, limbaugh and oreilly.
