<span style="text-decoration: underline">What motivates Domestic terrorists?</span>Death to: jews, blacks, @#%$, hispanics, doctors, the US government, judges, the UN, police, cutting down trees, animal testing, liberals and the media. Depends upon the particular terrorist group. 
<br />

<br />
When analysing a "terrorist" act in the US, one needs to look at the target. If the target is a representation of US power, projected onto the US, then the act was done by Domestic terrorists (for example, OKC and the anthrax letters). If the target is a representation of US power projected onto the rest of the world, then the act was not done by Domestic Terrorists (example 9/11).
