<br />

<br />
The Clinton way of dealing with the situation, (what was Clintons way of dealing with it?) clearly did not work.  After the first World Trade Center bombing, there were other terrorist attacks on the US as well, most notably was the ramming of the USS Cole.
<br />

<br />
I mention these two attacks because I know there is a tendency of some to want to belive that because a republican is President, the world hates the US and if we had a Democrat in office, this would somehow change.  
<br />

<br />
That being said, what I like about the Bush plan is we have provided a target closer to where the terrorists live. (Iran and Afganistan).  This is a very appealing target.  The easy choice is for the terrorists to attack us there, which means they are not attacking us in the US.  When they do attack us overseas, we are better able to flush them out.  There is also the added benefit of putting the terrorists in a reactionary mode, that is they are now reacting to things we have done rather then us reacting to them.  This gives us more control.
<br />

