				<td colspan="2" align="left"><div class="postbody"><a href="http://www.splcenter.org/legal/docket/files.jsp?cdrID=44" target="_blank" class="postlink">Oh look, another domestic terrorist group</a>.
<br />
<a href="http://www.svherald.com/articles/2003/12/20/news/news2.txt" target="_blank" class="postlink">And the local sheriff "claiming" they are not a problem</a>. Does this remind anyone else of the Branch Davidians? 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Balthemal wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">For example, I see lots of interviews with pissed off Iraqi's saying that they're ready to take up Jihad against the US forces. That's fine, it's easy to talk a good game, but when it comes down to it, when terrorist go head to head with coalition forces...they lose. And they lose HUGE. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"> The attacks on 9-11 were <span style="font-style: italic">theater</span>. They were not intending to be a military attack (in the sense of doing real damage). They were done to "feel good." Dieing in a suicide attack is a sign of <span style="font-style: italic">a good heart</span> to the primary audience of those actions: their compatriots. Pearl Harbor was an attack on military assets, and did significant damage to our military capacity (if the carriers had been there, it would have destroyed something like 95% of the Pacific US fleet, leaving Japan with uncontested military power in the Pacific for several months, by which time the US could not dislodge them). Knocking down the WTC was destroying a <span style="text-decoration: underline">symbol</span> of US economic power. It did very little actual damage to our economy. It did not destroy Wall Street, it did not destroy US trade with the world. Palestinian suicide bombing continues because it is <span style="font-style: italic">theater</span>, not because it is militarily or economically useful. Those who die get to show their <span style="font-style: italic">good heart</span> to those they leave behind.
<br />

<br />
Blowing up the Murrow building in OKC was also <span style="font-style: italic">theater</span>. McVeigh and his conspirators wanted to act out a scene in the Turner Diaries (the author of the Turner Diaries died in 2002). They believed that there was a groundswelling of anti-government frustration. The script in the play they were enacting would result in an armed uprising (overthrowing the US government) as a result of blowing up that building. 168 people died because of their fantasies. 
<br />

<br />
What happened the last time some thugs tried to blow up the WTC? They were hunted down and thrown in jail. What happened the last time some thugs decided to sit outside Langley and shoot folks going to work (at the CIA)? They were hunted down and thrown in jail. What happened when some thugs blew up the Murrow building? They were hunted down and thrown in jail. Nowadays we get <span style="font-style: italic">theater</span> masquerading as justice.
<br />

<br />
The invasion of Iraq is <span style="font-style: italic">theater</span>. It has no real excuse for happening. Nigerian yellowcake? fake. WMD? fake. WMD programs? fake. Able to launch WMD in 45 minutes? fake. Collusion with alqeda? fake. Intentions of WMD programs? another wet dream. Botox in a freezer? there is more in any botox party in Los Angeles. Aluminum rocket tubes going to be used for centrifuging U235/238? only in someone's imagination. Instead invasion of Iraq is a way for Bush to enact his fantasy of a crisis in Babylon, because that is what Revelations claims is needed for the end of the world. Being a rapturist, bush does not believe that he will need to die to enter heaven: just provoke the issues in Revelations in order to bring on the end times. And once the alleged rapture happens, he and his co-conspirators get sucked up to heaven leaving a mess behind that they don't have to care about. Rapturism is a two pronged evil: it is a denial of Christianity (while pretending to be devout Conservative Christianity, go go heresy) and it denies/prevents long term planning (the rapture is coming soon, therefore planning for the long term is denial of their most important beliefs). Pointing out the fallacy of the invasion gets you called a traitor, just like pointing out the emperor's new clothes would get you thrown in jail (when that fable happens in real life). The false dichotomy of the situation is that folks are claiming only 2 choices exist: support the invasion or support alqeda. They are blind to the fact that both of those choices are theater.
<br />

<br />
Dealing with people who are engaged in <span style="font-style: italic">theater</span> is like watching people masturbating: you can see that they are enjoying it, but by watching only their actions, you are missing more than 90% of what is going on. You cannot expect logical behavior from them. 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Most terrorists are uneducated and ill-equipped to do much damage short of blowing themselves up without leadership</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">. That is an American fantasy. The majority of suicide bombers and the 19 hijackers were college educated. Pretending that they were unwashed bumpkins is foolhardy and ultimately suicidal. Balthemal, you keep forgetting domestic terrorists. Anthrax letters? what anthrax letters? The script of bush's theater requires domestic terrorism to be forgotten. Pay no attention to the man behind the curtain!
<br />

<br />
